Photo credit: SABC By BO Staff Writer The following statement was previously published on the Black First Land First website: Xolani Gwala will be remembered as a fearless, sensitive but penetrating current affairs host on SABC1’s Asikhulume. His journalism at the public broadcaster remains exemplary. In one of the memorable shows on Asikhulume the focus was on land and the plight of farm workers in 2010. Gwala facilitated the conventional without biase or fear. Hamba kahle Mphepherwa … Issued by Black First Land First, National Coordinating Committee of (BLF NCC)
